Apollo4 OTP

Ambiq Micro Inc. OTP Registers

Copyright 2023 Ambiq Micro Inc.

Description:

This document details the contents of the Apollo4 Lite One Time Programmable registers.

OTP Index

0x5 		RSVD23
0x5 		AMB_SECBOOT_INST
0x5 		NVM_WIPE
0x0 		SRAM_WIPE
0x0 		AMB_SECURE_LOCK
0x0 		CUST_SECURE_LOCK
0x0 		DIS_CUST_INFO_PROG
0x0 		PLONEXIT
0x0 		CUST_SECBOOT
0x5 		AMB_CRYPTO_PUBLOCK
0x0 		RSVD_GPPC
0x00

Bits Name Type Flags Description
31:31 RSVD31 uint32_t Reserved field.
30:28 CUST_SECBOOTONRST uint32_t Enable secure boot at warm reset. All other encodings not listed will result in an error.
SBOREN = 0x2 - Secure boot on reset enable
SBORDIS = 0x5 - Secure boot on reset disabled. Only specific portions of secure boot flow are bypassed to allow for lower latency resume.
27:27 RSVD27 uint32_t Reserved field.
26:24 AMB_SECBOOT uint32_t Ambiq Secure Boot enable
SBEN = 0x2 - Secure boot enable
SBDIS = 0x5 - Secure boot disabled
23:23 RSVD23 uint32_t Reserved field.
22:20 AMB_SECBOOT_INST uint32_t Ambiq Secure Boot Install and Feature Enable. When enabled, secure boot feature is supported and the secure boot ROM (SBR) and secure boot loader (SBL) are pre-installed.
SBEN = 0x2 - Secure boot enable
SBDIS = 0x5 - Secure boot disabled
19:19 NVM_WIPE uint32_t NOT SUPPORTED ON RevB. When set, all main partition space in NVM in the device is wiped upon debugger attach.
18:18 SRAM_WIPE uint32_t NOT SUPPORTED ON RevB. When set, all SRAM in the device is wiped upon debugger attach.
17:17 AMB_SECURE_LOCK uint32_t Ambiq secure lock.
16:16 CUST_SECURE_LOCK uint32_t Customer Secure Lock. When set, this disables use of internal AI key overrides allowing access and programming to certain assets (e.g. INFO0). When clear, AI key is allowed to be activated.
15:12 DIS_CUST_INFO_PROG uint32_t Disable customer INFO space programming. Each bit corresponds to a quadrant of the INFO0. Note: these are disables since programming to a 1 will disable the corresponding INFO0 quadrant programming.
11:11 PLONEXIT uint32_t If configured to not lock it (value 0), the Secure Bootloader (SBL) keeps PROTLOCK open for customer secondary bootloader. This allows access to customer keybank area, if configured. In addition, PROTLOCK is used to deny/allow writing to the "Flash" (NVM) protection registers.

OTP_SECURITY:PLONEXIT should be set if no customer secondary bootloader is present. This ensures that the main images do not have the ability to change NVM protection. Moreover, it also locks the OTP keyband from general access once SBL exits.

When a secondary bootloader is present (OTP_SECURITY:PLONEXIT is 0), the secondary Bootloader should assert the PROTLOCK upon exit:

MCUCTRL->BOOTLOADER_b.PROTLOCK(write 1 to clear)

It is recommended to be done by Secondary Bootload on exit, but may be optionally kept open if the entire customer application is trusted.
PLNS = 0x1 - PROTLOCK No Seccondary bootloader. No secondary bootloader is provided, thus the Secure Bootloader (SBL) asserts PROTLOCK for protection of NVM and OTP keybank.
PLS = 0x0 - PROTLOCK by Secondary bootloader. The Secure Bootloader (SBL) keeps PROTLOCK open for the secondary bootloader. It is the responsibility of the secondary bootloader to assert PROTLOCK upon exit.
10:8 CUST_SECBOOT uint32_t Customer Secure Boot enable
SBEN = 0x2 - Secure boot enable
SBDIS = 0x5 - Secure boot disabled
7:5 AMB_CRYPTO_PUBLOCK uint32_t Ambiq Public side crypto Lock. When set, this disables use of crypto hardware services during non-secure mode.
Disabled = 0x5 - No decryption.
4:0 RSVD_GPPC uint32_t General purpose field reserved bits.

Description:
General purpose persistent configuration
